    "name": "Siw Malmkvist",
    "profile": "Swedish schlager singer and actress.\r\nBorn 31 December 1936 in Landskrona, Skåne County, Sweden.\r\nOlder sister of singer [a2349522].\r\nShe was married to actor [a=Fredrik Ohlsson (7)] until his death. \r\nOn 18 July 1964 she became the first Swede to have a hit on the US Billboard Hot 100 chart, when \"Sole Sole Sole\", a duet with Italian singer Umberto Marcato, entered the chart, peaking at No. 58. Malmkvist was especially popular in Scandinavia and West Germany, having a #1 hit in West Germany in 1964 with \"Liebeskummer lohnt sich nicht\". \r\n",
